<HEADLINE> ETrade to Add 2,200 Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ALPHARETTA, Ga. (AP) -- The online brokerage ETrade Group Inc.  
plans to add 1,900 to 2,200 employees at its Alpharetta office, 
while expanding its space by 450,000 feet. 
</P>
<P>
	The company has about 300 employees at its Alpharetta location.  
The expansion will occur over the next 2 1/2 years, said Jerry Dark, a 
vice president with ETrade, based in Palo Alto, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
	ETrade's first 700 additional employees are expected between  
January and June 2000. The company also has begun construction on a 
150,000- to 200,000-square-foot building. 
</P>
<P>
	The company now has one building in Alpharetta but envisions a  
corporate campus with four or five buildings housing customer 
service, marketing and financial services. 
</P>
<P>
	With 1998 revenues of $245 million, ETrade has more than doubled  
its customer accounts since launching its Destination ETrade Web 
site seven months ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Last week, the Internet brokerage signed up its millionth  
customer, a software publishing consultant from Roswell. 
</P>
