<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Buell Motorcycle Announces Recall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Buell Motorcycle Co. is recalling parts on  
nearly 19,000 motorcycles to correct possible problems. 
</P>
<P>
	The company, a division of Harley-Davidson Inc., was not aware  
of any injuries caused by the problems, Buell spokesman Joe Hice 
said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Among the problems are the front motor mount system in all  
1997-98 models; the negative battery cable in 1996-98 S1 Lightning 
and 1998 SI White Lightning models; and the rear brake line in 
Lightning X1 models. 
</P>
<P>
	Other problems are the side stand switch in 1996-98 models  
except the S2 and S2T Thunderbolt models; and the fuel tank 
retention system in 1995-99 models except the Lightning X1 models. 
</P>
<P>
	The company is also recalling the fuel tank vent in all 1995-99  
models; the swing arm suspension component supporting the rear 
wheel in all 1995-98 models and the shock absorber mounting point 
in all 1995-98 models. 
</P>
<P>
	Owners are being notified by letter and told to bring their  
motorcycles to dealers for repairs and replacement parts. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
