<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Quaker Oats Raises Cereal Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Quaker Oats Co. is joining other major cereal  
makers in raising prices, boosting prices of such brands as Cap'n 
Crunch and Life by about 3 percent, or about 8 cents a box. 
</P>
<P>
	The prices increases, which affect about 45 percent of the  
company's product line, will offset higher costs for labor, 
advertising and product improvements, company spokeswoman Margaret 
Eichman said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Quaker's announcement comes a month after General Mills Inc.  
said it would raise by 2.5 percent the price of its breakfast 
cereals. In December, Kellogg Co. raised the prices of its 
breakfast cereals by 2.7 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Richard Joy, an analyst with S&AMP;P Equity Group, said the  
companies are boosting prices to pay for additional advertising as 
they try to stem the recent trend among Americans toward eating 
``on-the-go'' foods instead of cereal for breakfast. 
</P>
<P>
	Joy also said Quaker's decision to raise prices may be partly  
opportunistic. 
</P>
<P>
	``As long as everybody goes up, it affords them the ability to  
go up as well,'' Joy said. 

</P>
</TEXT>
