<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> SI, Sport To Mark End of Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Sports Illustrated and Sport Magazine both are  
marking the end of the century with special features. 
</P>
<P>
	SI, in its issue out this week, lists its favorite dynasties of  
the 20th Century. No. 1 is the Boston Celtics from 1957-69. 
</P>
<P>
	The club won 11 NBA titles in those 13 years, led by Bill  
Russell and Bob Cousy and coached by Red Auerbach. 
</P>
<P>
	Notre Dame teams from 1946-49 are No. 2 on the list. In four  
years under coach Frank Leahy, Notre Dame went 36-0-2 and won three 
national titles. That dynasty produced Heisman Trophy winners 
Johnny Lujack and Leon Hart. 
</P>
<P>
	UCLA basketball in 1964-1976 is fourth followed by the New York  
Yankees teams from 1947-1962, winners of 10 championships. 
</P>
<P>
	Sport Magazine, in its next issue, presents baseball's top 10  
moments of the last 100 years. Jackie Robinson's historic debut 
with the Dodgers in 1947 tops the list, followed by Joe DiMaggio's 
56-game hitting streak in 1941. 
</P>
<P>
	Mark McGwire's record home run barrage last year is No. 4,  
behind Ted Williams putting his .400 batting average on the line in 
1941. None of the greatest moments of the century happened before 
1941, according to the panel of baseball people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
