<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Teaxs Executes Man for 1987 Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HUNTSVILLE, Texas (AP) -- A parolee who blamed his crimes on  
inhaling spray paint fumes was executed by injection Tuesday for 
stabbing and robbing a disabled Corpus Christi man. 
</P>
<P>
	Jose De La Cruz, 31, was on parole for burglary when he killed  
24-year-old Domingo Rosas, the boyfriend of a cousin. 
</P>
<P>
	De La Cruz had stopped legal maneuvers on his behalf.  
</P>
<P>
	``I've already made amends with myself,'' he said in a recent  
death row interview. ``I'm at total peace with my case. I'm not 
innocent. That man had every right to live just like I did.'' 
</P>
<P>
	De La Cruz, who was 19 at the time of the 1987 killing, stabbed  
Rosas while he was in a wheelchair and stole a television, video 
recorder and stereo. The victim's neck was also broken. 
</P>
<P>
	De La Cruz said his addiction to inhaling spray paint, beginning  
at age 10, got him high and allowed him to fantasize, contributing 
to his criminal behavior. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was mind-altering,'' he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
