<DOCNO> APW19990504.0076 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-04 23:25:06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> World Hockey Stars Selanne, Yashin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HAMAR, Norway (AP) -- After quick exits in the NHL playoffs,  
Teemu Selanne and Alexei Yashin are making the most of extended 
playing time in the World Hockey Championships. 
</P>
<P>
	Yashin has rediscovered his touch in Norway, scoring twice to  
lead Russia to a crucial 4-1 victory over newcomer Ukraine on 
Tuesday. Selanne was clearly still on a roll, scoring for Finland 
in his opening match against Belarus. 
</P>
<P>
	Yashin, who battled for the NHL scoring lead all season, was  
held scoreless as Buffalo swept Ottawa from the first round of the 
Stanley Cup playoffs, He's had no trouble finding the back of the 
net in the international tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	The powerful Russian has three goals in two games, leaving him  
just one short of the tournament's scoring lead. 
</P>
<P>
	Selanne, the NHL's leader this season with 47 goals for Anaheim,  
made his first appearance in the tournament despite having arrived 
on Sunday, after more than 15 hours in a plane. 
</P>
<P>
	``The first few games may be a bit difficult and it may take a  
couple of matches to get back in the swing,'' said a modest 
Selanne, making his third world championships appearance. ``But as 
the tournament goes on I'm sure I'll improve.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Not that Selanne has anything to prove or improve.  
</P>
<P>
	Winner of the newly established Maurice Richard trophy for the  
NHL's top scorer, Selanne has a long record of scoring brilliance. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1992-93, with the Winnipeg Jets (now the Phoenix Coyotes),  
Selanne and Alexander Mogilny became the NHL's top-scoring rookies 
with 76 goals. In 1997-98, Selanne shared the top spot on the NHL's 
scoring list with Peter Bondra with 52 goals. 
</P>
<P>
	But while Selanne's goal record is indisputably brilliant, it  
has never led to a major title or trophy. 
</P>
<P>
	In the NHL, Selanne has never won a Stanley Cup, nor has he won  
an Olympic or world championship title with Finland. 
</P>
<P>
	The closest the 28-year-old star came was in the Winter Games  
last year in Nagano, Japan, when Finland took the bronze medal. 
</P>
<P>
	``I wouldn't be here if I weren't interested in playing ... or  
winning,'' said Selanne, who scored six goals in the 1991 worlds in 
Finland and five goals in 1996 in Austria. ``I wanted to come 
because in my career I've won almost nothing and maybe I can change 
that here.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Today's schedule had the United States playing the Czech  
Republic -- both teams are 2-0 and already qualified for the next 
round; Canada vs. Italy; Japan vs. Austria; and Norway vs. 
Slovakia. 
</P>
<P>
	The two NHL stars will have a scoring showdown Thursday when  
Russia and Finland close out the round-robin portion of the 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	While Finland has already secured its place in the quarterfinal  
round, Russia's qualification hinges on the outcome of Thursday's 
match. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm not afraid,'' laughed Yashin, who scored 44 goals in the  
NHL regular season. ``Teemu is a very good friend of mine. We 
respect each other. He's a great scorer. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's probably going to be one of the most important matches  
for Russia and we'll need to prepare ourselves. They have a very 
good team with a lot of superstars from the NHL and they'll be a 
challenge for us. But we're not scared.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
