<HEADLINE> Pillsbury To Buy Hazelwood Bakeries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- The Pillsbury Co. plans to acquire Hazelwood  
Farms Bakeries from Supervalu Inc. for an undisclosed price. 
</P>
<P>
	Hazelwood Bakeries is one of the country's largest manufacturers  
of frozen dough to stores for making their own bakery products. 
</P>
<P>
	Pillsbury said in announcing the deal Tuesday that it should be  
completed in late May, subject to Federal Trade Commission 
approval. 
</P>
<P>
	Hazelwood Farms Bakeries employs more than 1,000 people in the  
United States at seven manufacturing facilities. 
</P>
<P>
	``The supermarket industry's trend toward consolidation has  
supermarkets turning toward larger, more focused suppliers for 
their in-store bakery products,'' said Paul Walsh, Pillsbury 
chairman and chief executive. ``This acquisition positions us as a 
key supplier, with a broad product offering in addition to 
providing the requisite sales and technical service.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Mike Wright, Supervalu chairman and chief executive, said the  
sale supports its plan to focus on its core food retailing and 
distribution businesses. Supervalu is based in Minneapolis. 
</P>
<P>
	Pillsbury, a Minneapolis-based subsidiary of Diageo PLC,  
produces a range of grocery items, frozen foods and refrigerated 
dough products for international consumer markets. The company is 
also supplies baking and other food products to the food service 
and commercial baking industries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
