<HEADLINE> La. Police Say Man Shot Accuser </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PONCHATOULA, La. (AP) -- A man who was about to go on trial on  
sexual assault charges Tuesday shot his accuser and killed her aunt 
as the women left for court, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	Witnesses told police that Aubrey LeBlanc Jr., 41, opened fire  
outside his accuser's home, killing her aunt, Donna Crenshaw, 37. 
The alleged victim of LeBlanc's sexual assault, who is 18, was in 
stable condition. 
</P>
<P>
	Police hunted for LeBlanc. His car was found at his home in  
nearby Metairie. 
</P>
<P>
	LeBlanc was arrested in June on charges of sexually assaulting  
the young woman, then 16, while he lived with her and her mother. 
The accuser was scheduled to testify against him. 
</P>
<P>
	He was allowed to remain free on bail during his trial. Jury  
selection was completed on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Ponchatoula is 40 miles northwest of New Orleans.  
</P>
