<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 'Cabaret' Honored at Hayes Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The composer and lyricists of such popular  
musicals as ``Cabaret'' ``Chicago'' and ``Kiss of the Spider 
Woman'' were singled out for a special award at the annual Helen 
Hayes Awards at the Kennedy Center. 
</P>
<P>
	John Kander and Fred Ebb were presented the annual American  
Express Tribute by actress Liza Minnelli, who said: ``If anyone 
asked me what I'm proudest of in my career, it's the music written 
for me by Kander and Ebb.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The award was one of many given out Monday night, with most  
going to local theater productions. For nonresident productions, 
Jane Lapotaire won best actress for ``All is True'' at the Kennedy 
Center and Alex Jennings for lead actor in ``Hamlet,'' also at the 
Kennedy Center. 
</P>
<P>
	The Charles MacArthur Award for outstanding new play, presented  
by Helen Hayes' son, James MacArthur, went to ``Lovers and 
Executioners.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
