<HEADLINE> Robber's Weapon: Hot Coffee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MONROE, La. (AP) -- Hot coffee was the weapon of choice, or maybe  
convenience, in a robbery Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	A man threw a cup of coffee at a clerk at a gas station  
convenience store, grabbed an undisclosed amount of money from the 
register and ran. 
</P>
<P>
	Derick Jones, 32, was arrested about 15 minutes later and booked  
for armed robbery. 
</P>
<P>
	The clerk suffered only minor burns.  
</P>
