<HEADLINE> Sonoco Buys Can Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HARTSVILLE, S.C. (AP) -- Packaging maker Sonoco has agreed to buy  
Crown Cork &AMP; Seal Co.'s composite can business for an undisclosed 
amount. 
</P>
<P>
	Sonoco announced the all-cash deal Tuesday.  
</P>
<P>
	The cans are made from paper, with metal or plastic ends, and  
are used for items such as refrigerated dough and snacks. 
</P>
<P>
	Philadelphia-based Crown Cork &AMP; Seal's composite can factories  
are in Massillon, Ohio; Murfreesboro, Tenn.; and Winter Garden, 
Fla. The division had sales of about $32 million last year. 
</P>
<P>
	Sonoco has 51 composite can operations worldwide, including 37  
in the United States. 

</P>
