Pittsburgh and sent New Jersey to another early playoff exit, 
leading the Penguins to a 4-2 win over the Devils in Game 7 of 
their opening-round series tonight. Jagr had two assists in the 
deciding game and helped set up another goal in a three-goal second 
period by Pittsburgh, which won despite managing only 13 shots. 
Martin Straka had a goal and two assists, and German Titov, Alexei 
Kovalev and Jan Hrdina added goals to advance the eighth-seeded 
Penguins to the second round against fourth-seeded Toronto in what 
is now a wide-open Eastern Conference. 

</P>
<P>
	AP NewsBrief by SUZANNE ROWLAND  

