<HEADLINE> Racists Convicted of Murderous Plot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LITTLE ROCK, Ark. (AP) -- Two white supremacists accused of  
plotting to set up a whites-only republic in the Pacific Northwest 
were convicted Tuesday of murder, conspiracy and racketeering. 
</P>
<P>
	Chevie Kehoe and Daniel Lee, both 26, could get the death  
penalty or life in prison without parole for killing an Arkansas 
gun dealer, his wife and her daughter in 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	The jury will return Thursday to begin hearing testimony in the  
sentencing phase. 
</P>
<P>
	Federal prosecutors said the men pursued their dream of an  
all-white republic by stockpiling military-style weapons, robbing 
several people and suffocating gun dealer William Mueller, his wife 
and her 8-year-old daughter. 
</P>
<P>
	The Aryan Peoples Republic was to have been perpetuated through  
polygamy, prosecutors said. 
</P>
<P>
	The conspiracy count charged that Kehoe and Lee also carried out  
crimes in other states, including two killings in Idaho and the 
1996 bombing of City Hall in Spokane, Wash. 
</P>
<P>
	But defense lawyers say that while Kehoe and Lee may have had  
offensive beliefs, they did not act criminally on them or have the 
means to do what prosecutors claim. 
</P>
<P>
	Chevie and brother Cheyne Kehoe first entered the public eye in  
1997, following a videotaped shootout with police in Ohio. Cheyne 
Kehoe later helped authorities find his brother. 
</P>
</TEXT>
